        <line>worst poet<add place="superlinear"> in other respects</add>, seems to have been
            purposely</line>
        <line>afforded as a divine evidence of the</line>
        <line>truth of this opinion<mod>
                <del rend="strikethrough">?</del>
                <add place="intralinear">.</add>
            </mod>
            <del rend="strikethrough">Do I a</del> Do you</line>
        <line>think with me o Ion.&#x2014; <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0003.01"/><hi
                rend="underline">Ion</hi><anchor xml:id="e1-0003.01"/> By Jupiter</line>
        <line>Ido. You touch <add place="superlinear">as it were</add> my soul with your wor<retrace
                cause="clarify">d</retrace>s</line>
        <line>o Socrates. <del rend="strikethrough">Exce</del>
            <del rend="strikethrough">The great poets</del> The</line>
        <line>excellent poets appear to me to be divinely</line>
        <line>commissioned as interpreters between the</line>
        <line>gods &amp; us.&#x2014; <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0003.02"/><hi
                rend="underline">Soc</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0003.02"/> Do not you rhapso</line>
        <line>-dists interpret the creations of the poets</line>
        <line><milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0003.03"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Ion</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0003.03"/> That also is true. <milestone
                unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0003.04"/><hi rend="underline">Soc</hi>.<anchor
                xml:id="e1-0003.04"/> You are then</line>
        <line>the interpreters of interpreters. <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0003.05"
                /><hi rend="underline">Ion</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0003.05"/></line>
